{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐργάζομαι</b>, <br /> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 18.469 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], etc., Cretan dialect <b>ϝεργάδδομαι</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“Schwyzer” 181v5 \">Refs</a>]: <i>future</i> <b>-άσομαι</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 1116 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>], etc., <i>Doric dialect</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ἐργαξοῦμαι 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 10.23, ἐργῶμαι “PCair.Zen.” 107.4 (3rd c.BC), LXX.Gen.29.27, +others, “IG” 7.3073.12 (Lebad., 2nd c.BC) (but 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus ἐργᾷ· ἐργάζει)\">LXX+3rd c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> εἰργασάμην, <i>Ionic dialect</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ἐργ- 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.115, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Th.” 845 (Lyric poetry), etc., 3rd._person_ etc for 1st._person_, 2nd._person_ _plural_ _optative_ ἐργασαίατο Aristophanes Comicus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Aves” 1147, “Lys.” 42; _Doric dialect_ ἠργάξαντο “SIG” 248 M (Delph., 4th c.BC)\">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> εἴργασμαι, <i>Ionic dialect</i>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ἔργ- 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.121.έ, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “fragment” 311, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —These tenses are used both in <i>middle</i> and <i>passive</i> <i>significations</i>: for other <i>passive</i> tenses, see below[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 111:— _Attic dialect_ Inscrr. of 4th C have ἠργαζόμην, ἠργασάμην, (ἐξ-) “IG” 22.1585.11, 1669.10, +others, but εἴργασμαι [prev. work]1666 A 27; so also ἠργάσατο [prev. work]7.424 (Oropus, 4th c.BC), εἰργασμένος [prev. work]3073.51 (Lebad., 2nd c.BC), ἐξήργασατο “UPZ” 19.8 (2nd c.BC), εἴργασμαι “PCair.Zen.” 146.3 (3rd c.BC)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; but this rule is often broken in later Papyrus, Inscrr., and codices:—<b>work, labour,</b> especially of husbandry, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Op.” 299, 309, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.72, etc.; but also of all manual labour, of slaves, ἐ. ἀνάγκῃ 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.272 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of quarrymen, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.124, etc.; τὴν οὐσίαν οὐ δικαζόμενον ἀλλ᾽ ἐργαζόμενον κεκτημένον 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 2.2.12 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. ἐν τοῖς ἔργοις in the mines, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 42.31: with _dative_ _instrumental_, χαλκῷ with brass, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Op.” 151; also of animals, βοῦς ἐργάτης ἐργάζεται 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “fragment” 563 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of birds <b>working</b> to get food, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “HA” 616b35 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of bees, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 625b22 \">Refs</a>]; of Hephaestus' self-acting bellows, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 18.469; τὸ χρῆμ᾽ ἐργάζεται\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] the matter <b>works,</b> i.e. <b>goes on,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ec.” 148 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὁ ἀὴρ ἐργάζεται <b>produces an effect</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Theophrastus Philosophus [{4-3rd c.BC}] “de Causis Plantarum” 5.12.7 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; οὐχ ὁμοίως ἐργάσεται τὸ θερμόν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 6.18.11. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>transitive</i>, <b>work at, make,</b> ἔργα κλυτά, of Athena, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 20.72, compare 22.422; ἀγάλματα, ὕμνους, 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 5.1, “I.” 2.46; τρίποδα, Νίκην, “SIG” 34 (Delph., 5th c.BC); ἁμαξίδας Aristophanes Comicus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Nubes” 880; οἰκοδόμημα 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.76 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; εἰκόνας, ἀνδριάντας, καλὰ ἔργα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Cra.” 431c, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Mem.” 2.6.6, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Men.” 91d; κηρόν, σχαδόνας, of bees, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “HA” 627a6, 30; μέλι 2nd c.AD: Soranus Medicus “Vit. Hippocr.” 11 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>make</b> so and so, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ξηρὸν ἐ. τινά 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “DMar.” 11.2; μέγαν Aelianus [{2-3rd c.AD}] “Varia Historia” 3.1 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]. <br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>do, perform,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ἔργα ἀεικέα 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 24.733 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἔργον ἐπ᾽ ἔργῳ ἐ., of husbandmen, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Op.” 382, compare 397; ἐργασίας ἐ. 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1121b33, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Oec.” 7.20; ἐναίσιμα, φίλα ἐ., 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 17.321, 24.210; θαυμαστά Plato Philosophus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Symposium” 213d; περὶ θεοὺς ἄδικον μηδέν [prev\\. author] “Grg.” 522d \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. πρᾶγμα, opposed to βουλεύειν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ant.” 267, compare “OT” 347; τὸ ἔργον Κυρίου NT.1Cor.16.10 \">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>double</i> <i>accusative</i>, <b>do</b> something <b>to..,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" τά περ νῦν ἐ. [ὁ ἥλιος] τὸν Νεῖλον 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.26 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], etc.; chiefly in bad sense, <b>do</b> one ill, <b>do</b> one a shrewd turn, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" κακὰ ἐργάζεσθαί τινα 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 786, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.137, etc.; so οἷά μ᾽ εἰργάσω, τί μ᾽ ἐργάσε; 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ph.” 928, 1172 (Lyric poetry), etc.; μὴ δῆτα τοῦτό μ᾽ ἐργάσῃ [prev\\. author] “El.” 1206; αἴσχιστα ἐ. τινά Aristophanes Comicus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Vespae” 787 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; less frequently, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ἀγαθὰ ἐ. τινά 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.79, compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.52, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Cri.” 53a; πολλὰ καὶ καλὰ τὴν Ἑλλάδα [prev\\. author] “Phdr.” 244b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; seldom [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" τινί τι Aristophanes Comicus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Vespae” 1350; οἷν ἐμοὶ δυοῖν ἔργ᾽ ἐστὶ κρείσσον᾽ ἀγχόνης εἰργασμένα 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1374 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]. <br /><Level4><b>__II.2.b</b></Level4> <b>perform</b> rites, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" τὰ ἱερὰ ἐ. “1st Epistle to the Corinthians” 9.13 \">Refs</a>]. <br /><Level4><b>__II.2.c</b></Level4> in Law, ζημίαν ἐ. <b>do</b> damage, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Isaeus Orator 6.20, compare 4th c.BC: Hyperides Orator “Ath.” 22. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>work</b> a material, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ὅπλα..οἷσίν τε χρυσὸν ἐργάζετο 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 3.435 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. γῆν <b>till</b> the land, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.17, etc.; ἐ. [ἀγροὺς] ἐργάταις Xenophon Historicus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.6.11; γῆν καὶ ξύλα καὶ λίθους [prev\\. author] “HG” 3.3.7 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; [ἀργυρῖτιν] Docum. cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 37.28; ἐ. θάλασσαν, of traders, 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 3.46; γλαυκὴν ἐ., of fishers, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Th.” 440. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> <b>earn by working,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" χρήματα 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.24, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Eq.” 840, etc.; καινὸν βίον ἐκ τοῦ δικαίου Andocides Orator [{5-6th c.BC}] 1.144, compare 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Op.” 43; ἀργύριον ἀπὸ σοφίας Plato Philosophus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Hp.Ma.” 282d; μισθοῦ τὰ ἐπιτήδεια Xenophon Historicus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Memorabilia” 2.8.2 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]. <br /><Level3><b>__II.5</b></Level3> <b>work at, practise,</b> μουσικήν, τέχνας, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phd.” 60e, “R.” 374a, etc.; ἐπιστήμας Xenophon Historicus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Oeconomicus” 1.7 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; ἀρετὴν καὶ σωφροσύνην variant in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 13.6; δικαιοσύνην, ἀνομίαν, NT.Acts.10.35, NT.Matt.7.23. \">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.6</b></Level3> <i>absolutely</i>, <b>work at a trade</b> or <b>business, traffic, trade,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ἐν [γναφείῳ] 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 23.2; ἐν ἐμπορίῳ καὶ χρήμασιν 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 36.44; ἐν τῇ ἀγορᾷ [prev\\. author] 57.31 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] (also οἱ τὴν τετράγωνον (i.e. ἀγοράν) ἐργαζόμενοι those who <b>trade in</b> the square, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“BCH” 8.126 (compare “Glotta” 14.73)); κατὰ θάλατταν 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 56.48 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; τούτοις..ναυτικοῖς ἐ. <b>trade</b> with this money on bottomry, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev\\. author] 33.4; δὶς ἢ τρὶς ἐ. τῷ αὐτῷ ἀργυρίῳ [prev\\. author] 56.30 \">Refs</a>]; ταῦτα ἐ. thus he <b>trades,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev\\. author] 25.82; οἱ ἐργαζόμενοι _traders,_ [prev\\. author] 34.51 \">Refs</a>]; οἱ ἐν Δήλῳ ἐ., = Latin <i>qui Deli negotiantur</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“CIG” 2285b; especially of courtesans, σώματι ἐ.,\">Refs</a>] Latin <i>quaestum corpore facere,</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 59.20; ἐπὶ τέγους ἀπὸ τοῦ σώματος 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 12.13.2 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ἀπὸ τῆς ὥρας Alexis Sam. cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 13.572f, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Tim.” 14. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.7</b></Level3> <b>cause,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" κολακείην 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 268; πημονάς 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 326; πόθον τινί 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 61.11; σύριγγας ἀνιάτους 7th c.AD: Paulus Aegineta Medicus 6.44 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. <br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>passive</i>, rarely in <i>present</i> and <i>imperfect</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 8.87 (ἐξ-), 4th c.BC: Hyperides Orator “Eux.” 35 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: <i>future</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ἐργασθήσομαι 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 1218, (ἐξ-) 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator “Ep.” 6.8 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> εἴργασμαι (see. below): <i>aorist 1</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" εἰργάσθην Plato Philosophus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Respublica” 353a, 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “HP” 6.3.2, etc. \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.1</b></Level3> <b>to be made</b> or <b>built,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ἔργαστο τὸ τεῖχος 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.179; ἐκ πέτρας εἰργασμένος Aeschylus Tragicus [{4-5th c.BC}] “Prometheus Vinctus” 244; οἰκοδόμημα διὰ ταχέων εἰργ. 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.8 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; λίθοι εἰργ. <b>wrought</b> stones, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev\\. author] 1.93; γῆ εἰργ. Xenophon Historicus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Oeconomicus” 19.8; θώρακας εὖ εἰργ. [prev\\. author] “Mem.” 3.10.9 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]. <br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <b>to be done,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Ag.” 354, 1346, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hec.” 1085; εἰργασμένα _things done, deeds, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.53 (ἐργ-), 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 1281, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “OT” 1369. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G2038","accentedUnicode":"ἐργάζομαι","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G2039","matchingForm":"ἐργασία","stepTransliteration":"ergasia","gloss":"work","_zh_tw_Gloss":"生意","_es_Gloss":"obra","_zh_Gloss":"生意"},{"strongNumber":"G2040","matchingForm":"ἐργάτης","stepTransliteration":"ergatēs","gloss":"worker","_zh_tw_Gloss":"工人","_es_Gloss":"obrero","_zh_Gloss":"工人"},{"strongNumber":"G2041","matchingForm":"ἔργον","stepTransliteration":"ergon","gloss":"work","_zh_tw_Gloss":"行為, 工作, 事","_es_Gloss":"obra","_zh_Gloss":"行为, 工作, 事"},{"strongNumber":"G2110","matchingForm":"εὐεργέτης","stepTransliteration":"euergetēs","gloss":"benefactor","_zh_tw_Gloss":"恩主","_es_Gloss":"benefactor","_zh_Gloss":"恩主"},{"strongNumber":"G2716","matchingForm":"κατεργάζομαι","stepTransliteration":"katergazomai","gloss":"to workout/produce","_zh_tw_Gloss":"行, 作","_es_Gloss":"llevar a cabo/producir","_zh_Gloss":"行, 作"},{"strongNumber":"G4020","matchingForm":"περιεργάζομαι","stepTransliteration":"periergazomai","gloss":"be a busybody","_zh_tw_Gloss":"好管閒事","_es_Gloss":"ser un entrometido","_zh_Gloss":"好管闲事"},{"strongNumber":"G4021","matchingForm":"περίεργος","stepTransliteration":"periergos","gloss":"meddlesome/magic","_zh_tw_Gloss":"邪術, 好管閑事","_es_Gloss":"entrometido/magia","_zh_Gloss":"邪术, 好管闲事"},{"strongNumber":"G4333","matchingForm":"προσεργάζομαι","stepTransliteration":"prosergazomai","gloss":"to earn more","_zh_tw_Gloss":"已經賺了","_es_Gloss":"ganar más","_zh_Gloss":"已经赚了"},{"strongNumber":"G4903","matchingForm":"συνεργέω","stepTransliteration":"sunergeō","gloss":"to work with","_zh_tw_Gloss":"同工","_es_Gloss":"trabajar con","_zh_Gloss":"同工"},{"strongNumber":"G4904","matchingForm":"συνεργός","stepTransliteration":"sunergos","gloss":"co-worker","_zh_tw_Gloss":"同工","_es_Gloss":"colaborador","_zh_Gloss":"同工"}],"shortDef":"to work, be active, accomplish (something)","mediumDef":"to work, be active, accomplish (something) <br />intrans. <b>to work, labor,</b> <ref='Mat.21.28'>Mt. 21:28</ref>; <ref='Luk.13.14'>Lk. 13:14</ref>; <b>to trade, traffic, do business,</b> <ref='Mat.25.16'>Mt. 25:16</ref>; <ref='Rev.18.17'>Rev. 18:17;</ref> <b>to act, exert one's power, be active,</b> <ref='Jhn.5.17'>Jn. 5:17</ref>; <i>transitive</i> <b>to do, perform, commit,</b> <ref='Mat.26.10'>Mt. 26:10</ref>; <ref='Jhn.6.28'>Jn. 6:28</ref>; <b>to be engaged in, occupied upon,</b> <ref='1Co.9.13'>1Cor. 9:13;</ref> <ref='Rev.18.17'>Rev. 18:17;</ref> <b>to acquire, gain by one's labor,</b> <ref='Jhn.6.27'>Jn. 6:27</ref>","stepGloss":"to work","stepTransliteration":"ergazomai","count":41,"_es_Definition":"intrans. trabajar ; comerciar, invertir (MAT.25:16) ; trans. hacer, producir ; llevar a cabo (tareas del templo) ; trabajar para (JN.6:27) ; vivir del mar, comerciar por mar (APOC.18:17)","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 工作, 勞動, 幹活<br>2) 做, 作出<br> 2a) 執行, 進行, 作<br> 2b) 生產, 作出來<br> 2c) 掙得, 獲得 (約 6:27)","_zh_Definition":"1) 工作, 劳动, 干活<br>2) 做, 作出<br> 2a) 执行, 进行, 作<br> 2b) 生产, 作出来<br> 2c) 挣得, 获得(约6:27 )","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"làm việc. Xem G2041","_zh_tw_Gloss":"作工, 作, 行","_es_Gloss":"trabajar","_zh_Gloss":"作工, 作, 行"}]}